normalized_sections.tailrisk:risk-aware ml framework pypi |g:
Tech Stack: Python, Scikit-learn, CVaR/LaR Loss, Meta-learning, PyPI

- Developed and published the TailRisk package on PyPI, establishing a framework for predicting extreme insurance losses.

- Engineered a Hybrid Meta-Learner architecture with Quantile and LaR optimization to overcome traditional MSE model failure.

- Achieved a 10.25% reduction in CVaR (95%) and a 3.21% drop in 99th-percentile MSE invalidation on 69K+ insurance claims.

- Ensured production readiness through full Scikit-learn API compatibility and automated GitHub Actions testing.

- Provided candidates with instant profiling by engineering automated transparency reports and LaTeX resume optimization.
